{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.31",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 31,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 31",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 31 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:1",
      "text": "I made a covenant with mine eyes; why then should I think upon a maid?",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:2",
      "text": "For what portion of God is there from above? and what inheritance of the Almighty from on high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:3",
      "text": "Is not destruction to the wicked? and a strange punishment to the workers of iniquity?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:4",
      "text": "Doth not he see my ways, and count all my steps?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:5",
      "text": "If I have walked with vanity, or if my foot hath hasted to deceit;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:6",
      "text": "Let me be weighed in an even balance, that God may know mine integrity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:7",
      "text": "If my step hath turned out of the way, and mine heart walked after mine eyes, and if any blot hath cleaved to mine hands;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:8",
      "text": "Then let me sow, and let another eat; yea, let my offspring be rooted out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:9",
      "text": "If mine heart have been deceived by a woman, or if I have laid wait at my neighbour’s door;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:10",
      "text": "Then let my wife grind unto another, and let others bow down upon her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:11",
      "text": "For this is an heinous crime; yea, it is an iniquity to be punished by the judges.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:12",
      "text": "For it is a fire that consumeth to destruction, and would root out all mine increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:13",
      "text": "If I did despise the cause of my manservant or of my maidservant, when they contended with me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:14",
      "text": "What then shall I do when God riseth up? and when he visiteth, what shall I answer him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:15",
      "text": "Did not he that made me in the womb make him? and did not one fashion us in the womb?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:16",
      "text": "If I have withheld the poor from their desire, or have caused the eyes of the widow to fail;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:17",
      "text": "Or have eaten my morsel myself alone, and the fatherless hath not eaten thereof;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:18",
      "text": "(For from my youth he was brought up with me, as with a father, and I have guided her from my mother’s womb;)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:19",
      "text": "If I have seen any perish for want of clothing, or any poor without covering;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:20",
      "text": "If his loins have not blessed me, and if he were not warmed with the fleece of my sheep;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:21",
      "text": "If I have lifted up my hand against the fatherless, when I saw my help in the gate:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:22",
      "text": "Then let mine arm fall from my shoulder blade, and mine arm be broken from the bone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:23",
      "text": "For destruction from God was a terror to me, and by reason of his highness I could not endure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:24",
      "text": "If I have made gold my hope, or have said to the fine gold, Thou art my confidence;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:25",
      "text": "If I rejoiced because my wealth was great, and because mine hand had gotten much;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:26",
      "text": "If I beheld the sun when it shined, or the moon walking in brightness;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:27",
      "text": "And my heart hath been secretly enticed, or my mouth hath kissed my hand:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:28",
      "text": "This also were an iniquity to be punished by the judge: for I should have denied the God that is above.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:29",
      "text": "If I rejoiced at the destruction of him that hated me, or lifted up myself when evil found him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:30",
      "text": "Neither have I suffered my mouth to sin by wishing a curse to his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:31",
      "text": "If the men of my tabernacle said not, Oh that we had of his flesh! we cannot be satisfied.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:32",
      "text": "The stranger did not lodge in the street: but I opened my doors to the traveller.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:33",
      "text": "If I covered my transgressions as Adam, by hiding mine iniquity in my bosom:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.34",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:34",
      "text": "Did I fear a great multitude, or did the contempt of families terrify me, that I kept silence, and went not out of the door?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.35",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:35",
      "text": "Oh that one would hear me! behold, my desire is, that the Almighty would answer me, and that mine adversary had written a book.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.36",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:36",
      "text": "Surely I would take it upon my shoulder, and bind it as a crown to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.37",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:37",
      "text": "I would declare unto him the number of my steps; as a prince would I go near unto him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.38",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:38",
      "text": "If my land cry against me, or that the furrows likewise thereof complain;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.39",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:39",
      "text": "If I have eaten the fruits thereof without money, or have caused the owners thereof to lose their life:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.31.40",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 31,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 31:40",
      "text": "Let thistles grow instead of wheat, and cockle instead of barley. The words of Job are ended.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
